<div id="attachment_46422" class="wp-caption alignnone" ><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-large wp-image-46422" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-1200x800.jpg" alt="farmer spraying pesticide" width="1200" height="800" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-520x347.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-768x512.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones-900x600.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/7-agricultural-drones.jpg 2000w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Farmers who choose not to implement drones in their work continue to spray pesticides manually, as shown here.</p></div>
<hr />
<div id="attachment_46423" class="wp-caption alignnone" ><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-column-width wp-image-46423" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-900x1349.jpg" alt="A mobile phone—next to a remote controller—shows a map of a field that will be sprayed by a drone. " width="900" height="1349" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-900x1349.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-520x780.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-1200x1799.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/8-agricultural-drones.jpg 1334w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A mobile phone—next to a remote controller—shows a map of a field that will be sprayed by a drone.</p></div>
<hr />
<div id="attachment_46424" class="wp-caption alignnone" ><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-large wp-image-46424" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-1200x800.jpg" alt="Drone pilot Thanh Sang tests a visor-based photographic drone in his free time. " width="1200" height="800" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-520x347.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-768x512.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones-900x600.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/9-agricultural-drones.jpg 2000w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Drone pilot Thanh Sang tests a visor-based photographic drone in his free time.</p></div>
